So. There is a new baby in your life. Whether it's your friends, yours, a family members, and you really want to buy them a beautiful book! All you can think of are the classics, and you just know that everyone else is running along those same lines of thought.
<br>&nbsp;

Well, here is a handy list of a couple of my favorites that are clever, cute, and most of all, shouldn't make a parent dread re-reading them a million times (ok anything read that many times might get a little boring no matter how good but these should last a while!).

[Little Pea by Amy Krouse Rosenthal illustrated by Jen Corace](http://www.brooklinebooksmith-shop.com/book/9781452142890)

<br>![](data:image/png;base64,)Meet Little Pea. He is a happy little guy who loves hanging out with his pea pals, playing with Papa Pea, and snuggling with Mama Pea. But one thing Little Pea doesn't like is CANDY (which is what Peas eat for dinner apparently). But to get to dessert (spinach - Little Pea's FAVORITE) he has to finish every bite of dinner! Blech!

---

also by Rosenthal and Corace:

[Little Hoot](http://www.brooklinebooksmith-shop.com/book/9781452152073)

![](data:image/png;base64,)Little Hoot is a sleepy little owl who just wants to go to bed! But Mama and Papa say that to grow up to be a wise old owl Little Hoot has to stay up LATE! He tries all kinds of things to stay awake, all the while counting down the minutes until he can curl up in bed and have sweet dreams.

I love how Rosenthal takes classic parenting problems and flips them around. Instead of craving candy, Little Pea wants veggies! Instead of begging to stay wake Little Hoot only wants to sleep! Clever little jokes, and the adorable illustrations make these cute, funny, light hearted board books a must!

---

[The Gossie and Friends series by Olivier Dunrea](http://www.brooklinebooksmith-shop.com/search/author/%22Dunrea%2C%20Olivier%22)

No series of board books gives me more joy than this one! Simple, quick, but full of character, you will quickly become attached to this group of adorable ducklings! There's Gossie and Gertie, Booboo, Peedie, Gus, Jasper and Joop, Gemma, Ollie, and Gideon. I couldn't possibly pick a favorite, and you can often find me reading them to myself (or coworkers) on slower days.

[Shh! We Have A Plan](http://www.brooklinebooksmith-shop.com/book/9780763679774) and [Oh No, George! by Chris Haughton](http://www.brooklinebooksmith-shop.com/book/9780763676520)

Haughton has a great sense of humor and his color palates are beautiful! His board books are full of emotion and humor, and give you the room to add your own bits and pieces to the story.
